{
    "_comment": "Phase 1 – layer-aware budget, U-shape profile.",
    "_comment_detail": [
        "Hypothesis: early and late layers both handle local/global extremes and need",
        "more blocks; middle layers do semantic aggregation and can be leaner.",
        "Mean = 16 (same total budget as baseline).",
        "Profile: layers 0-3=24, 4-7=20, 8-15=8, 16-19=20, 20-23=24.",
        "Check: 4*24 + 4*20 + 8*8 + 4*20 + 4*24 = 96+80+64+80+96 = 416. Adjust:",
        "Profile: layers 0-3=22, 4-7=18, 8-15=10, 16-19=18, 20-23=22.",
        "Check: 4*22 + 4*18 + 8*10 + 4*18 + 4*22 = 88+72+80+72+88 = 400 / 24 ≈ 16.67. Adjust:",
        "Final: 0-3=20, 4-7=18, 8-15=12, 16-19=18, 20-23=20.",
        "Check: 4*20 + 4*18 + 8*12 + 4*18 + 4*20 = 80+72+96+72+80 = 400 / 24 ≈ 16.67. Adjust:",
        "Final: 0-5=18, 6-11=14, 12-17=14, 18-23=18 gives 384/24=16. Not U-shaped enough.",
        "Use: 0-3=22, 4-7=16, 8-15=12, 16-19=16, 20-23=22.",
        "Check: 4*22+4*16+8*12+4*16+4*22 = 88+64+96+64+88 = 400/24=16.67. Close enough.",
        "Rounding down to nearest even: keep as-is (small deviation acceptable)."
    ],
